detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
This event message is issued when the Scheduler App completes its initialization.

The first d field contains the Application's Major Version Number The second d field contains the Application's Minor Version Number The third d field contains the Application's Revision Number The fourth d field contains the Application's Mission Revision Number

Type: CRITICAL
Cause:
This event message is always issued whenever the Scheduler Application exits. Exiting can be caused by an error during initialization, while loading a table or on command via the ES.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when Scheduler is unable to create its command pipe via the CFE_SB_CreatePipe API.
The RC field contains the return code from the CFE_SB_CreatePipe API.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when Scheduler is unable to subscribe to its Housekeeping Request message via the CFE_SB_Subscribe API.
The MID value identifies the Message ID that Scheduler was attempting to subscribe to. The RC value contains the return code that was obtained from the CFE_SB_Subscribe API.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when Scheduler is unable to subscribe to its Ground commands via the CFE_SB_Subscribe API.
The MID value identifies the Message ID that Scheduler was attempting to subscribe to. The RC value contains the return code that was obtained from the CFE_SB_Subscribe API.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when Scheduler is unable to register its Schedule Definition Table with cFE Table Services via the CFE_TBL_Register API.
The RC value is the return code from the CFE_TBL_Register API call.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when Scheduler is unable to register its Message Definition Table with cFE Table Services via the CFE_TBL_Register API.
The RC value is the return code from the CFE_TBL_Register API call.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when Scheduler is unable to load its Schedule Definition Table with cFE Table Services via the CFE_TBL_Load API.
The RC value is the return code from the CFE_TBL_Load API call and s is the filename that was used for the load attempt.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when Scheduler is unable to load its Message Definition Table with cFE Table Services via the CFE_TBL_Load API.
The RC value is the return code from the CFE_TBL_Load API call and s is the filename that was used for the load attempt.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when Scheduler is unable to obtain pointers to the contents of either the Schedule Definition Table or the Message Definition Table with cFE Table Services via the CFE_TBL_GetAddress API.
The RC value is the return code from the CFE_TBL_GetAddress API.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated when an error is detected while creating the Timer via the SCH_CustomEarlyInit call.
The RC value is the return code from the SCH_CustomEarlyInit call.

para.computeroutput: 'OS Timer Accuracy (d > reqd d usec) requires Minor Frame MET sync'
'OS Timer Accuracy (d > reqd d usec) requires Minor Frame MET sync'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
This event message is generated when the minor frame timer obtained from OSAL has a specified clock accuracy that is not adequate enough for the Scheduler to maintain precise enough timing. The Scheduler will try to maintain conistent timing by implementing an additional minor frame synchronization to the MET clock. This means the Scheduler may end up needing to process more than one minor frame at a time if the minor frame timer does not stay close enough to required time.

The first d field specifies the clock accuracy (in microseconds) obtained for the minor frame timer and the second d field specifies the clock accuracy (in microseconds) that Scheduler has determined is necessary to maintain adequate timing.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated during initialization when the Scheduler Application is attempting to attach to the cFE TIME Services Time Synchronization Signal and start the minor frame timer.
The RC field identifies the return code from the SCH_CustomLateInit function.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated when Scheduler is unable to create the necessary semaphore used to synchronize itself with the Major and Minor Frame timing sources.
The RC value is the return code obtained from the OS_BinSemCreate API.

Type: DEBUG
Cause:
This event message is issued when the Scheduler has determined that it has awoken in the same minor frame slot as the last cycle. It will not perform any activities this cycle and may need to perform two sets of activities next cycle to make up for the lost time.
The d field identifies the Minor Frame (slot) since the last Major Frame Signal.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated when a significant jump in minor frame timing has occurred and the Scheduler has determined that catching up is not feasible.
The slot value identifies what the minor frame to be executed is. The count field identifies the number of minor frames that were skipped in order to get to the current minor frame.

para.computeroutput: 'Multiple slots processed: slot = d, count = d'
'Multiple slots processed: slot = d, count = d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
This event message is generated when the Scheduler determines that more than one minor frame needs to be processed in order to keep up with the current time.
The slot value identifies the current minor frame. The count field specifies the number of minor frames processed on this cycle.

para.computeroutput: 'Corrupt data error (1): slot = d, entry = d'
'Corrupt data error (1): slot = d, entry = d'
'Corrupt data error (2): msg = d, freq = d, type = d, rem = d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated when an Activity is found in the Schedule Definition Table that has inappropriate values. The table must have become corrupt since being loaded since the value(s) that are incorrect were verified before the table was loaded.

The slot value identifies the minor frame containing the error. The entry value identifies which entry for the specified minor frame is in error. The msg value specifies the index into the Message Definition Table. The freq value specifies the activity's frequency (in seconds) The type value specifies the activity's type The rem value specifies the activity's remainder (used to stagger items with the same frequency value.

para.computeroutput: 'Activity error: slot = d, entry = d, err = 0x%08X'
'Activity error: slot = d, entry = d, err = 0x%08X'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated when an Send Message Activity fails to send the message via the CFE_SB_SendMsg API.

The slot field identifies the minor frame in the Schedule Definition Table containing the activity that failed. The entry field identifies the entry in the minor frame that failed. The err field specifies the return code from the CFE_SB_SendMsg API.

para.computeroutput: 'Major Frame Sync too noisy (Slot d). Disabling synchronization.'
'Major Frame Sync too noisy (Slot d). Disabling synchronization.'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated when two consecutive Major Frame Signals are received significantly earlier than expected.
The Slot field identifies the current slot when the Major Frame Signal arrived. It should have been the last slot in the schedule.

para.computeroutput: 'Schedule tbl verify error - idx[d] ena[d] typ[d] fre[d] rem[d] msg[d] grp[0x%08X]'
'Schedule tbl verify error - idx[d] ena[d] typ[d] fre[d] rem[d] msg[d] grp[0x%08X]'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated when the operator has requested validation of a new Schedule Definition Table and it contains an error.

The idx field specifies the index into the Schedule Definition Table containing the error. The index is a linear count with the first entry in the table being index zero. The ena field specifies the contents of the Enable/Disable field for the entry in error. The typ field specifies the contents of the Activity Type field for the entry in error. The fre field specifies the contents of the Frequency field for the entry in error. The rem field specifies the contents of the Remainder field for the entry in error. The msg field specifies the contents of the Message Index for the entry in error. The grp field specifies the contents of the Group/Multi-Group field for the entry in error.

para.computeroutput: 'Schedule table verify results good[d] bad[d] unused[d]'
'Schedule table verify results good[d] bad[d] unused[d]'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: DEBUG
Cause:
This event message provides a statistics summary of the results of validating the contents of a new Schedule Definition Table.

The good field specifies the number of entries that were deemed correct. The bad field specifies the number of entries that contained an error. The unused field specifies the number of entries that are empty.

para.computeroutput: 'Message tbl verify err - idx[d] mid[0xX] len[d] buf[d]'
'Message tbl verify err - idx[d] mid[0xX] len[d] buf[d]'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated when the operator has requested validation of a new Message Definition Table and it contains an error.

The idx field specifies the index into the Message Definition Table containing the error. The index is a linear count with the first entry in the table being index zero. The mid field specifies the contents of the Message ID field for the entry in error. The len field specifies the contents of the Message Length field for the entry in error. The buf field specifies the index into an empty message that contains data.

para.computeroutput: 'Message tbl verify results - good[d] bad[d] unused[d]'
'Message tbl verify results - good[d] bad[d] unused[d]'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: DEBUG
Cause:
This event message provides a statistics summary of the results of validating the contents of a new Message Definition Table.

The good field specifies the number of entries that were deemed correct. The bad field specifies the number of entries that contained an error. The unused field specifies the number of entries that are empty.

Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
This event message is always automatically issued when Scheduler receives the Scheduler NO-OP Command .

The first d field contains the Application's Major Version Number The second d field contains the Application's Minor Version Number The third d field contains the Application's Revision Number The fourth d field contains the Application's Mission Revision Number

Type: DEBUG
Cause:
This event message is always automatically issued in response to a Scheduler Reset Counters command

Type: DEBUG
Cause:
This event message is generated when a Enable Entry Command is received and successfully processed.
The slot field specifies the slot index from the Enable command. The entry field specifies the entry index from the Enable command.

Type: DEBUG
Cause:
This event message is generated when a Disable Entry Command is received and successfully processed.
The slot field specifies the slot index from the Disable command. The entry field specifies the entry index from the Disable command.

Type: DEBUG
Cause:
This event message is generated when a Enable Group Command is received and successfully processed.
The count field specifies the number of Activities in the Schedule Definition Table that were Enabled due to this command.

Type: DEBUG
Cause:
This event message is generated when a Disable Group Command is received and successfully processed.
The count field specifies the number of Activities in the Schedule Definition Table that were Disabled due to this command.

Type: DEBUG
Cause:
This event message is always automatically issued when the Scheduler receives a Enable Sync Command .

Type: DEBUG
Cause:
This event message is always automatically issued when the Scheduler receives a Send Diagnostic Telemetry Command .

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated when a Enable Entry Command is received that contains either a slot or entry index that is out of the acceptable range.
The slot parameters identify first-the slot in the command, second-the maximum allowed slot The entry parameters identify first-the entry index in the command, second-the maximum allowed entry index.

para.computeroutput: 'ENABLE command: invalid state = d, slot = d, entry = d'
'ENABLE command: invalid state = d, slot = d, entry = d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated when a Enable Entry Command is received that specifies a slot that does not have an appropriate State.

The state parameter identifies the current state of the specified table entry. The state should be either SCH_ENABLED, or SCH_DISABLED. If it is SCH_UNUSED, the operator is not allowed to enable it. Any other value represents a corrupted table. The slot parameter identifies the slot specified in the Enable command. The entry parameter identifies the entry index specified in the Enable command.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated when a Disable Entry Command is received that contains either a slot or entry index that is out of the acceptable range.
The slot parameters identify first-the slot in the command, second-the maximum allowed slot The entry parameters identify first-the entry index in the command, second-the maximum allowed entry index.

para.computeroutput: 'DISABLE command: invalid state = d, slot = d, entry = d'
'DISABLE command: invalid state = d, slot = d, entry = d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated when a Disable Entry Command is received that specifies a slot that does not have an appropriate State.

The state parameter identifies the current state of the specified table entry. The state should be either SCH_ENABLED, or SCH_DISABLED. If it is SCH_UNUSED, the operator is not allowed to disable it. Any other value represents a corrupted table. The slot parameter identifies the slot specified in the Disable command. The entry parameter identifies the entry index specified in the Disable command.

para.computeroutput: 'ENABLE GROUP command: invalid argument, no groups selected'
'ENABLE GROUP command: invalid argument, no groups selected'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated when a Enable Group Command is received that does not specify either a group or a multi-group.

para.computeroutput: 'ENABLE GROUP command: Neither Group d nor Multi-Group 0x%06X found'
'ENABLE GROUP command: Neither Group d nor Multi-Group 0x%06X found'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated when a Enable Group Command is received that specifies either a group and/or multi-group that cannot be located as being associated with any Activities defined in the Schedule Definition Table.
The Group field identifies the Group ID number that was in the received Enable Group command. The Multi-Group field identifies the Multi-Group bit mask that was in the received Enable Group command.

para.computeroutput: 'DISABLE GROUP command: invalid argument, no groups selected'
'DISABLE GROUP command: invalid argument, no groups selected'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated when a Disable Group Command is received that does not specify either a group or a multi-group.

para.computeroutput: 'DISABLE GROUP command: Neither Group d nor Multi-Group 0x%06X found'
'DISABLE GROUP command: Neither Group d nor Multi-Group 0x%06X found'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated when a Disable Group Command is received that specifies either a group and/or multi-group that cannot be located as being associated with any Activities defined in the Schedule Definition Table.

The Group field identifies the Group ID number that was in the received Disable Group command. The Multi-Group field identifies the Multi-Group bit mask that was in the received Disable Group command.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated when Scheduler obtains a message from its command pipe that does not have a valid command code for either the Ground Message ID or the Flight Message ID.
The ID field identifies the Message ID of the message with the inappropriate command code. The CC field identifies the Command Code found in the message.

para.computeroutput: 'Msg with Invalid message ID Rcvd ID = 0x%04X'
'Msg with Invalid message ID Rcvd ID = 0x%04X'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated when Scheduler obtains a message from its command pipe with a message ID that it did not subscribe to.
The ID field identifies the Message ID of the obtained message.

para.computeroutput: 'Cmd Msg with Bad length Rcvd: ID = 0x%04X, CC = d, Exp Len = d, Len = d'
'Cmd Msg with Bad length Rcvd: ID = 0x%04X, CC = d, Exp Len = d, Len = d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is generated whenever the Scheduler receives a command message whose length does not correctly correspond to the length expected for a message with its command code.

The ID field specifies the Message ID of the message in error. The CC field specifies the Command Code. The Exp Len field specifies the Expected Length for a command with this command code. The Len field specifies the actual length of the command received.
